{"lemma":"ظاهِرٌ","slug":"ظاهِرٌ","root":"ظ.ه.ر","root_slug":"ظ-ه-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ظ-ه-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"ظاهِر","root":"ظهر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":8},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n27733"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B8%D8%A7%D9%87%D9%90%D8%B1%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to help, to assist, to aid, to support"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"apparent, visible"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"evident, obvious"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"face"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"surface"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"what is apparent (as opposed to what is unseen, invisible)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"exterior","examples":[{"text":"بَاطِنُهُ فِيهِ الرَّحْمَةُ وَظَاهِرُهُ مِن قِبَلِهِ الْعَذَابُ","english":"On the near side will be grace and on the far side will be torment."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of ظَهَرَ (ẓahara)."},"ipa":["/ðˤaː.hi.ru/","/ðˤaː.hir/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n27733","headword_ar":"ظَاهِرٌ","root":"Zhr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Outward, exterior, external, extrinsic,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exoteric:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and hence,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"appearing, apparent, overt, open, perceptible"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perceived, manifest, conspicuous, ostensible, plain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evident:"},{"kind":"text","text":"in all these senses]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baATinN","text_ar":"بَاطِنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K, TA:) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZahiyrN","text_ar":"ظَهِيرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) [Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZaAhirFA","text_ar":"ظَاهِرًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Outwardly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"apparently;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY AlZ~aAhiri","text_ar":"فِى الظَّاهِرِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in appearance."},{"kind":"text","text":"And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlZ~aAhiru A^an~ahu ka*aA","text_ar":"الظَّاهِرُ اَنَّهُ كَذَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It appears,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it seems,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what seems to be the case is, that it is so,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thus."},{"kind":"text","text":"And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZaAhiru ka*aA","text_ar":"ظَاهِرُ كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZaAhirN fiyhi ka*aA","text_ar":"ظَاهِرٌ فِيهِ كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning A person, or thing,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in whom,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which, such a quality is apparent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manifest,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: see an ex. in a verse cited in the first paragraph of art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TEn","text_ar":"طعن"},{"kind":"text","text":".] See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muZoharN","text_ar":"مُظْهَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  [Hence also,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EayonN ZaAhirapN","text_ar":"عَيْنٌ ظَاهِرَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A prominent eye;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that fills its cavity."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA","text_ar":"هٰذَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amorN ZaAhirN Eanoka EaAruhu","text_ar":"اَمْرٌ ظَاهِرٌ عَنْكَ عَارُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is a thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an affair, of which the disgrace is remote from thee:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"does not cleave to thee."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA EayobN ZaAhirN Eanoka","text_ar":"هٰذَا عَيْبٌ ظَاهِرٌ عَنْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is a vice,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fault, that does not cleave to thee."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) A poet says, (namely, Kutheiyir, accord. to a copy of the S, or Aboo-Dhu-eyb, TA,)"},{"kind":"quote","text":"waEay~arahaA AlwaA$uwna A^an~iY A^uHib~uhaA\n                      \n                     \n                        watiloka $akaApN ZaAhirN Eanoka EaAruhaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And the slanderers taunted her with the fact of my loving her; but that is a fault of which the disgrace is remote from thee"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, TA.) ―         -b4-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlZ~aAhiru","text_ar":"الظَّاهِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The outside,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exterior,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing. You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nazala ZaAhira Almadiynapi","text_ar":"نَزَلَ ظَاهِرَ المَدِينَةِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He alighted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"took up his abode, outside the city:"},{"kind":"text","text":"comp."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZaAhirapN","text_ar":"ظَاهِرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZaAhiru Alkaf~i","text_ar":"ظَاهِرُ الكَفِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZaAhiru","text_ar":"ظَاهِرُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alqadami","text_ar":"القَدَمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and another signification of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZaAhirN","text_ar":"ظَاهِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": for all of which see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZahorN","text_ar":"ظَهْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", third quarter. ―         -b5-  [Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The external, outward,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extrinsic, state, condition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"circumstances,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a man: and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the outward,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"apparent, character,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disposition of the mind:"},{"kind":"text","text":"opposed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbaATinu","text_ar":"البَاطِنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b6-  One says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN ZaAhirN","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ ظَاهِرٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY fulaAnK","text_ar":"عَلَى فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one has the ascendancy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mastery, over such a one; is conqueror of him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"victorious over him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA A^amorN","text_ar":"هٰذَا اَمْرٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZaAhirN bika","text_ar":"ظَاهِرٌ بِكَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is a thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an affair, that overcomes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"overpowers, thee."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA A^amorN","text_ar":"هٰذَا اَمْرٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anota bihi ZaAhirN","text_ar":"اَنْتَ بِهِ ظَاهِرٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is an affair which thou hast power to do."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa ZaAhirN EalaY ka*aA","text_ar":"هُوَ ظَاهِرٌ عَلَى كَذَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is a conqueror, a winner, an achiever,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an attainer, of such a thing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see an ex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garabN","text_ar":"غَرَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", near the end.] And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlZ~aAhiru","text_ar":"الظَّاهِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is one of the names of God, meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Ascendant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Predominant, over all things:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He who is known -by inference of the mind from what appears to mankind of the effects of his actions and his attributes."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, TA.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAjatuhu Einodaka ZaAhirapN","text_ar":"حَاجَتُهُ عِنْدَكَ ظَاهِرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His want is in thine estimation"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an object of contempt,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"neglect, as though"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cast behind the back."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, * TA.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaraA^ahu ZaAhirFA","text_ar":"قَرَاَهُ ظَاهِرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZahorN","text_ar":"ظَهْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", towards the end of the paragraph.       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aA='N ZawaAhiru","text_ar":"شَا=ءٌ ظَوَاهِرُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sheep,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goats, that come to the water every day at noon."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%B8%D8%A7%D9%87%D8%B1/","headword_ar":"ظاهر","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_18","lexicon_en":"Al-Sharīf al-Jurjānī, Kitāb al-Taʿrīfāt (d. 1413 CE)","lexicon_ar":"كتاب التعريفات للشريف الجرجاني","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=23394#5f4577","body_html":"<span>الظاهر: هو اسم لكلام ظهر المراد منه للسامع بنفس الصيغة، ويكون محتملًا للتأويل والتخصيص.<br></span><br>الظاهر: ما ظهر المراد منه للسامع بنفس الكلام، كقوله تعالى: {وَأَحَلَّ اللَّهُ الْبَيْعَ} . وقوله تعالى: {فَانْكِحُوا مَا طَابَ لَكُمْ} . وضده، الخفي، وهو ما لا ينال المراد إلا بالطلب كقوله تعالى: {وَحَرَّمَ الرِّبا} .<br><br>ظاهر العلم: عبارة -عند أهل التحقيق- عن أعيان الممكنات.<br><br>ظاهر الوجود: عبارة عن تجليات الأسماء، فإن الامتياز في ظاهر العلم حقيقي والوحدة نسبية، وأما ظاهر الوجود فالوحدة حقيقية والامتياز نسبي.<br><br>ظاهر الممكنات: هو تجلي الحق بصور أعيانها وصفاتها، وهو المسمى بالوجود الإلهي، وقد يطلق عليه: ظاهر الوجود، وظاهر المذهب، وظاهر الرواية، المراد بهما: ما في المبسوط، والجامع الكبير، والجامع الصغير، والسير الكبير، والمراد بغير ظاهر المذهب والرواية: الجرجانيات، والكيسانيات، والهارونيات."}]}}